  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1275984266" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1275984266" />
    <a title="Asha Ketharam" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/42720276-asha-ketharam"><img alt="Asha Ketharam" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1447150377p2/42720276.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1275984266?book_show_action=true">May 09, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Asha Ketharam" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Asha Ketharam" href="/user/show/42720276-asha-ketharam">Asha Ketharam</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1275984266" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10452322659437563108">‘Grow old along with me!<br/>The best is yet to be,<br/>The last of life, for which the first was made....’<br/>- Robert Browning<br/><br/>How many are really lucky to grow old with a life companion, - who will be a part of the life sharing, caring, loving, a companion to look into each other’s eyes, smile soulfully and when the day ends to laugh over the happenings of the day and when the next day dawns to smile and say, &apos;whatever be, we shall be together and wait...for the BEST is yet to Be!&apos;<br/>‘Chase of choices’,- is un</span>
  <span id="freeText10452322659437563108" style="display:none">‘Grow old along with me!<br />The best is yet to be,<br />The last of life, for which the first was made....’<br />- Robert Browning<br /><br />How many are really lucky to grow old with a life companion, - who will be a part of the life sharing, caring, loving, a companion to look into each other’s eyes, smile soulfully and when the day ends to laugh over the happenings of the day and when the next day dawns to smile and say, 'whatever be, we shall be together and wait...for the BEST is yet to Be!'<br />‘Chase of choices’,- is undoubtedly a book written with words soaked in emotions,- anxiety, fear of the unknown, the excitement of the feeling of love, the melancholy of a soul left alone, the solitude of a man left alone to take care of kids, with a hope of finding a companion to share his love and making a home of love and passion.<br />The book runs through 46 chapters worked in detail that the reader finds it hard to close on any one of them to take a break! It is indeed a book tempting you to finish at one go as the writer makes the reader travel along with him in his journey of searching for his companion and in the search of his love. The book is a narrative in simple words, easy to read and keeps one thinking.<br />Before you start reading the book, you wonder that probably it is a book related to the character of Ravi’s choice of marriage and the events that followed that led him to the chase of choices. Little is said about Ravi’s married life but whatever little is said speaks of the painful relationship experienced. Once you start reading, you realise that it is a search for a new life, a new companionship, the thirst of finding someone who would fill the vacuum in the family life, the vacuum of love and caring that goes missing when one parent moves away.<br />The initial chapters give you the realistic picture for those life companion hunters in the matrimonial market, the revelations, the secrets the anonymity that goes in the profiles, of how different person perceive what to reveal and what not to. It in a way reflects on personalities, how they prefer to be known to a totally new person and how much they reveal once they get to know the person well. One can understand the different personalities of the four women who the main character of the story, Ravi seeks for his future companionship. <br />The four women discussed in the book have their own differences but have a common trait of wanting to be loved. All of them have experienced an emptiness in their marital lives though they have been very eventful in the negative sense of it, each woman undergoing different kinds of tortures. As for the character Ravi, the portrayal of his character is a strong character as he is seen by his colleagues and friends. But as one flips through the pages, one realises the insecurity of the character, the person’s longing to get someone to love and be loved. <br />The arrival of the character, Olivia, brings in a surprise to readers of how one person can actually become the focus of one's life, leaving all the other things to lesser priority and weakness of the human mind to be at the receiving end when there is shower of love. Olivia’s presence in Ravi’s life seems to be to quench the thirst of Raj in his travel of finding his new love. As one reads through the chapters the reader hope that that the family vacuum will be filled against all the odds. <br />The character of Olivia also brings out the fact that every human in spite of the profession he or she is in, is made of those same feelings as far as love and companionship is concerned and makes one realise that even a therapist goes through the roller coaster ride of security and insecurity and the need to love and to be loved. Indeed, the healer too needs some healing and some soft and kind words to keep the rhythm in life going. The Character of Olivia, is a blend of a strong professional woman with passion at the same time weak when it comes to her own feelings of love and wanting. She can be easily lured by someone who is prepared to give her love, who can be really impulsive in her pursuit for getting the love of a man.<br />Once can try to relate the attachment theory about those who survive attachments and those who do not survive attachments based on the childhood experience and security of love during childhood. This book is definitely one good piece to be read and the characters can help you understand the various psychological theories that explain love and attachment.<br />At the end of the book, one is left with lingering thoughts about the meaning of marriage, relationships, and the emptiness when one companion leaves the home. All the five characters are in the same journey in different directions, hoping for a new entry in their lives to give love. ‘Love is not love unless it is given away’. There are so many in real life who have not met real love and one wishes all those similar characters in the book to get what they deserve. Nothing is fair in the game of love and war. Yes, indeed, the journey of the characters continue in their chase of the choices, as,- the best is yet to be!<br />The book is to be read by all… those who are in relationships, in marriage, those who decide that they had enough of their marriage mirage and who want to step into a new world in search of new love as it gives insights on the struggles one faces in turbulent relationships and trouble that comes after the end of a strained relationship. Indeed the chase goes on as long as the human race is satisfied with love and companionship. <br />The book also sends a strong message that whatever be the pursuit of the parents in and out of the marriages, the children carry a lot of anxiety, mixed emotions and challenges in their innocent minds that needs to be taken seriously.<br />Order your copy today and read for yourself the choices and the chase… one takes up to find what is right. Can love be easily found and conquered? Read for yourself to know the answers!<br /><br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://soulful18.wordpress.com/2014/10/25/book-review-on-chase-of-choices-by-dr-hari-parameshwar/">https://soulful18.wordpress.com/2014/...</a><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="10452322659437563108" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


