<div id="review_1292886084" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1292886084" />
    <a title="Book&#39;d Hitu" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5610463-book-d-hitu"><img alt="Book&#39;d Hitu" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1326779417p2/5610463.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1292886084?book_show_action=true">May 29, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Book&#39;d Hitu" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Book&#39;d Hitu" href="/user/show/5610463-book-d-hitu">Book&#39;d Hitu</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5610463-book-d-hitu?shelf=review-copy">review-copy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5610463-book-d-hitu?shelf=indian-writings">indian-writings</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1292886084" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8203571547730744535"><b>The Story</b><br/>Ravi Raj Nambiar, is a divorced father in search of a life partner who can support him and his two children, a boy and a girl namely Kittu and Kini respectively. Through his impressive profile on IDM, he starts receiving different interests from women from different parts of country including one from an irresistible woman named Olivia Claire from US.<br/><br/>One fine day Olivia lands in India and then subsequently in the city where Ravi lives and then the story becomes quite happening with unex</span>
  <span id="freeText8203571547730744535" style="display:none"><b>The Story</b><br />Ravi Raj Nambiar, is a divorced father in search of a life partner who can support him and his two children, a boy and a girl namely Kittu and Kini respectively. Through his impressive profile on IDM, he starts receiving different interests from women from different parts of country including one from an irresistible woman named Olivia Claire from US.<br /><br />One fine day Olivia lands in India and then subsequently in the city where Ravi lives and then the story becomes quite happening with unexpected twists and turns. Ravi becomes so engrossed with her and developed the liking for Olivia that he rejected two women with whom he was on talking terms for building a life together. <br /><br /><b>The Characters</b><br />All the characters viz. Ravi, Kittu and Kini, Anjali, Minu and Priya are finely developed and described in such a wonderful manner that the reader immediately feels attached to them.<br /><br />Olivia is a character that is in main lead after Ravi. She was wonderful in all aspects when it comes to claim Ravi as her own during the incidents occurred in her visit to India.<br /><br />I really liked and adored the character of Ravi, being a single parent and his hard efforts to make the ends of his professional and family life meet. Still, I developed a dislike for Ravi for a while when he indulged into the sexual encounter on his very first meeting with Olivia. But more on the other side, his character is portrayed in a very positive way which the readers will adore and feel his pains throughout the book.<br /><br /><br /><b>Synopsis</b><br />The roller coaster ride is something which gives you all possible excitement and thrills while it lasts and at the end it leave you exactly where you have started. This is how you will feel when you go through this book.<br /><br />The finale chapter was amazing and shocking for me as the author decided to reveal a surprise for the readers.<br /><br />One more thing I loved about the book was the last paragraph of each chapter. This contained deep insights about leading a happy life and relationships. Even those last paragraphs can be separately published as an insightful book.<br /><br /><b>Disclaimer</b><br />I must thank Dr. Hari Parmeshwar for providing me a personalized review copy of this book.<br />This review is a summary of my own thoughts and views about the book and is in no way biased.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8203571547730744535" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


