        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1274766973" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9616828476244752460">&quot;Chase of Choices&quot; A very suitable title given for this book. I read very less book due to busy schedule, but this book made me more queries by chapter to chapter to read full book. I thought Ravi chasing will be end after getting Meenu, may be by Anjali, or Olivia, but it engaged me in never-ending selection of choices. <br/>I ask reader, if you think that you are better decision taker then read this book and decide which choice is better? I am sure, you will get confused. Just reading first chapter</span>
  <span id="freeText9616828476244752460" style="display:none">"Chase of Choices" A very suitable title given for this book. I read very less book due to busy schedule, but this book made me more queries by chapter to chapter to read full book. I thought Ravi chasing will be end after getting Meenu, may be by Anjali, or Olivia, but it engaged me in never-ending selection of choices. <br />I ask reader, if you think that you are better decision taker then read this book and decide which choice is better? I am sure, you will get confused. Just reading first chapter itself creates lot of questions in mind. Characters like Meenu proved that understanding Mars may be easier than understanding physiology of women.<br />A very interesting book and I feel it must read book for those who think that you are better decision taker.<br />I wanted to highlight a quote:<br />“God, grant me serenity to accept the things I can't change, courage to change the things I can, and the wisdom to know the difference"<br />-page: 29, from Chase of choices by Dr. Hari Parameshwar."<br /><br /></span>
