<div id="review_1292025849" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1292025849" />
    <a title="Vamsi " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11670657-vamsi"><img alt="Vamsi " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1533531528p2/11670657.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1292025849?book_show_action=true">May 28, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Vamsi " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Vamsi " href="/user/show/11670657-vamsi">Vamsi </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11670657-vamsi?shelf=2015">2015</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1292025849" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15903192635696139455"><b>Chase of Choices is not my cup of tea</b><br/><br/>It&apos;s the story of 45 year old Ravi Raj.Divorced and father of two kids.In his search for a suitable lady to be his wife and a good mother to his children. He met 4 women of different mentalities and had to choose one of them to be his soul-mate. This 302 pages book is his journey with them.Unfortunately, I find nothing but emotional drama in this novel.<br/><br/>On a scale of 1 to 5 I&apos;d rate this novel on certain specifications a writer must meet to write a good novel<br/>-</span>
  <span id="freeText15903192635696139455" style="display:none"><b>Chase of Choices is not my cup of tea</b><br /><br />It's the story of 45 year old Ravi Raj.Divorced and father of two kids.In his search for a suitable lady to be his wife and a good mother to his children. He met 4 women of different mentalities and had to choose one of them to be his soul-mate. This 302 pages book is his journey with them.Unfortunately, I find nothing but emotional drama in this novel.<br /><br />On a scale of 1 to 5 I'd rate this novel on certain specifications a writer must meet to write a good novel<br />-&gt;<i>Entertaining</i>:<b>2</b><br />-&gt;<i>Emotions</i>:<b>4</b><br />-&gt;<i>Plot</i>:<b>2.5</b><br />-&gt;<i>Character</i>:<b>2</b><br />-&gt;<i>Setting</i>:<b>1</b><br /><br />The entire novel there were only two things going on: Ravi having a conversation.Ravi thinking.<br />Nothing was described about setting throughout the novel,except for one scene. What his place looks like? What his office look like? There is a lot of scope to describe about setting so that reader would relieve from emotional scenes he just read. A reader want to live in a story not read it,a novel will always be incomplete without setting.<br /><br />Coming to the plot: Ravi got a problem.He got to solve it,and he did find ways to solve it.By updating his matrimony profile and meeting 4 women.Fine! For first 10-12 chapter everything's good. <br />Having conversation,analyzing who will suit the need,Communicating emotionally,for next 5 chapters same plot,next 5 chapter same plot,rest of the novel almost same plot. <br />We laugh at a hilarious joke for 1st time we hear it,what if the same joke is told 10 times and expected us to laugh? Same analogy.<br /><i>At starting he's alone and met 4 women.By the ending he's alone losing 4 women,which brings us to starting.So nothing much happened except for emotional whining of 5 person.</i><br /><br />Coming to character: Same joke analogy is applied to Ravi.I felt happy for him as he was working out his life caring for his children but as the story progressed due to over recalling of inner emotions,feelings author made him a desperate,a cyber stalker,emotionally hurt,lonely person,lost and seeking approval from the world.<br /><br /><br />I'd like to read novels to get entertained despite the genre. How could I get entertained when every time I open the book finding the words were filled with sorrow, misery, depression, sadness, loneliness, cheating, rejection, impatience, desperation.<br />It's psychology,brain releases stress inducing hormone cortisol upon reading these emotions which will eventually make reader stressed out. That's why I rated entertainment:2<br /><br />Although Author did a great job through his wisdom by writing wise quotes,those are like valuable drops in this ocean type novel.<br />I have one word for this novel:<b>Mature</b>.This novel is so mature that I'd only recommend it to people of age over 30. May be I'm not mature enough to read this novel,but I can surely say that my opinion on this would be changed if I read it after 10 years. <br /><br />A great attempt which has to be read by a few circle of people. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="15903192635696139455" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


